Package: UnivRankR
Type: Package
Title: Fuzzy Multi-Criteria Decision Making with BWM Integration
Version: 0.2.1
Author: Marek Deja
Maintainer: Marek Deja <marek.deja@uj.edu.pl>
Description: Implements fuzzy MCDM methods (TOPSIS, VIKOR, WASPAS) for decision-making problems.
    Includes an automated data preparation pipeline for scaling raw data (Likert, continuous)
    to Saaty's 1-9 scale and fuzzifying it. Features an integrated Best-Worst Method (BWM)
    solver for calculating criteria weights using linear programming.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: Rglpk, ggplot2, ggrepel, RankAggreg, stats
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
NeedsCompilation: no
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5)
